race.comment: Siding with BERKSHIRE BREEZE (6) out to 2500m off two very nice runs this time in, finding the line strongly behind Caulfield Cup favourite Half Yours in the G3 Naturalism second up over 2000m. He was no match there but is building nicely and if they're positive early he'll go close. GILDED WATER (15) is the one with all the upside, far too good for BM84 company last start and now dropping 4.5kg. The trip will suit and no doubt he's very progressive but that's certainly been factored into early markets. REVELARE (2) kept his winning streak intact with a tough win in the G3 Archer Stakes here last time, booking his Melbourne Cup spot. Up in the weights now and this does attract a Cup penalty if he were to win it. INTERPRETATION (7) has been solid to the line in two runs back and can peak third up to 2500m. MORMONA (12) is consistent and should be thereabouts.
